### Repository Pattern
- Repositories are the single source of truth for a feature's data
- Implement caching when appropriate (remote success → cache; offline → local)
- Handle connectivity gracefully via `NetworkInfo` (or equivalent)
- Map data models (DTOs) to domain entities before returning `Right(...)`
- Catch data-source exceptions and return `Left(Failure)` — do not leak exceptions to domain/presentation
- Expose clear method signatures on the domain repository interface
- Handle pagination and fetching details inside the repository or dedicated use cases, not in the UI
